                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus from="157vc" to="158rc"/>
                           <desc type="Letter">A letter from <persName ref="PRS7830Petros"><roleName type="function">Metropolitan</roleName>Ṗeṭros IV</persName> to the community of <placeName ref="INS0105DD">Dabra Dāmmo</placeName>.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">መልእክት፡ ዘፈነዋ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ሊቀ፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ዘመንግሥተ፡ ኢትዮጵያ፡ ገብሩ፡ ወሐዋርያሁ፡ ለክርስቶስ፡ ወልዱ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ማርቆስ፡ ወንጌላዊ፡ ትብጻሕ፡ ኀበ፡ <sic>ውሉዱየ</sic>፡ ፍቁራንየ፡ ቡሩካን፡ ወቅዱሳን፡ ማኅበረ፡ ደብረ፡ ዳሞ፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">A letter sent by Ṗeṭros, the metropolitan of the kingdom of Ethiopia, the servant and Apostle of Christ, the son of Saint Luke the Apostle, may it reach to my beloved children, the blessed and the holy community of Dabra Damo … </q>
                           <note>The introduction is written in Gǝʿǝz whereas the main body in Amharic. The letter was most likely written by <persName ref="PRS7830Petros">Ṗeṭros IV</persName> who arrived in Ethiopia in <date>1881</date> during
                              the reign of <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs IV</persName>. Another letter of the metropolitan is contained in the manuscript <ref type="mss" corresp="ESqdgm003"/>.</note>
                        </item>
